    {
      "id": "91f1bc96dc7bbba7355937fed7ff859164e91ef0",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-24 17:41:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> What about LDLM_ENQUEUE?\n\nWe have it as ldlm_ibits_enqueue.\n\n \nt:lustre-release# cat /proc/fs/lustre/mds/MDS/mdt/stats \nsnapshot_time             1411580422.751382 secs.usecs\nreq_waittime              24873 samples [usec] 22 5103 13196933 13022906531\nreq_qdepth                24873 samples [reqs] 0 17 933 5931\nreq_active                24873 samples [reqs] 1 2 30780 42594\nreq_timeout               24873 samples [sec] 1 10 24900 25170\nreqbuf_avail              51969 samples [bufs] 63 64 3325105 212749327\nldlm_ibits_enqueue        2521 samples [reqs] 1 1 2521 2521\nmds_getattr               3 samples [usec] 108 170 386 52228\nmds_connect               29 samples [usec] 49 843 6850 2205988\nmds_getstatus             3 samples [usec] 45 135 255 25875\nmds_statfs                7 samples [usec] 72 195 840 110078\nmds_sync                  85 samples [usec] 6538 9823 707870 5926438784\nmds_get_info              170 samples [usec] 78 298 27807 4845177\nmds_hsm_state_get         170 samples [usec] 87 333 27939 5003715\nmds_hsm_progress          255 samples [usec] 28 549 44878 14365434\nmds_hsm_request           85 samples [usec] 464 1528 68173 57128139\nmds_hsm_ct_register       340 samples [usec] 23 4347 52669 127060573\nmds_hsm_ct_unregister     340 samples [usec] 25 114 14624 713538\nobd_ping                  20075 samples [usec] 16 717 877278 45602108",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "1b7db3c3782e2d59a9afe81fb2fc7099c9aae38e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-24 20:09:18.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWould it be better as ldlm_enqueue_ibits, so that it is more easily searched by the RPC name (LDLM_ENQUEUE) and it would sort with other types of enqueue if they are added in the future?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "7c5bdb5c187bd3ddf7620504aaeffcdac6d97002",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-26 20:23:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAre we allowed to change the names of these stats?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "36f173e392b82e0ba10b017faa204e67292fbcfc",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-26 20:24:38.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n(I agree that ldlm_enqueue_ibits would be better.)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "b76346f5d4d522b67391bea78c46c554345b5c73",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-09-27 08:26:29.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nIt wouldn't hurt to ask the IML and LMT folks to see if they are monitoring the ldlm stats using this specific name. Our own tools just reformat the stats and don't care about the specific names. \n\nAurelien, does Shine check the ldlm_ibits_enqueue stats?\n\nI suspect that it is _probably_ not used by anyone, but I can't say for sure. \n\nOne option would be to print the same stat with both names, but that might cause extra complexity since I think this proc output is generated from the stats table directly and it would be bad to have to keep duplicate stats just to print out the name twice. \n\nGetting a test for the validity of these stats would be nice.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "2fe507f5a2e5fff240e6c4a3e605dab7e634e039",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 217,
        "name": "Aurelien Degremont",
        "email": "aurelien.degremont@cea.fr",
        "username": "adegremont",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-09-29 08:06:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nShine does not use this stats.\n\nHowever, our local admin tools do. I think other site graphing this statistics will have some compat issue. We will have to adapt our scripts between 2.5 and 2.7+. This is not a big deal but there definitely will be a compat issue there.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
